## Selected academic projects

### Intraspecific trait variability in freshwater fish communities

This project investigated whether individual-level trait variability modifies estimates of functional diversity in freshwater fish assemblages from French Guiana.

The study compared functional spaces calculated using individuals and species centroids, showing that species-level approaches can underestimate functional space and mask biologically relevant variability.

### Predator identity and vegetation effects on gammarid survival

This project assessed how predator communities and habitat structure influence prey survival in coastal ecosystems. The results emphasized the protective role of vegetation cover and the importance of predator identity in shaping ecological interactions.

### Discarded fishing gear and coral reef monitoring

This project focused on the impact of discarded fishing gear on coral reefs and contributed to field-based monitoring protocols in tropical marine ecosystems.

